{"cursor":"1178","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'']] A 'loment' (or 'lomentum') is a type of indehiscent\nlegume fruit that breaks apart at constrictions occurring between segments, so\nthat each segment contains one seed. It is a type of schizocarp.\n\nTick trefoil ([[Desmodium]]) and sweet vetch ([[Hedysarum]]) are two genera that\nexhibit this fruit type, which is found particularly in the Hedysareae tribe of\nthe family Fabaceae.\n","linknr":143,"url":"Loment","recorded":1376422346,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Loment&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Loment&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loment","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.visualEditor.viewPageTarget.noscript&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/File:Hedysarum_hedysaroides_2005.08.03_10.36.20.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/11/Hedysarum_hedysaroides_2005.08.03_10.36.20.jpg/250px-Hedysarum_hedysaroides_2005.08.03_10.36.20.jpg","/wiki/File:Hedysarum_hedysaroides_2005.08.03_10.36.20.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.22wmf12/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","/w/index.php?title=Hedysarum_hedysaroides&action=edit&redlin